question
Write a function named convertNumber that takes a positive integer decimal number num as an argument and
returns an array in decimal, binary, octal, and hexadecimal notation.
Examples:
convertNumber (5) should return [5, 101, 5, 5];
convertNumber (9) should return [9, 1001, 11, 9];
convertNumber (12) should return [12, 1100, 14, "c"];
convertNumber (32) should return [32, 100000, 40, "20"]

solution:

function convertNumber(num){
  let a = Number(num.toString());
  let b = Number(num.toString(2));
  let c = Number(num.toString(8));
  let d = Number(num.toString(16));
  return [a, b, c, d];
}
